<body>

  
    <div class="recipe-container">
        <h1>🥙 Stuffed Paratha Recipe</h1>
       

        <h2>Ingredients:</h2>
        <ul class="ingredients-list">
            <li>2 cups Whole Wheat Flour</li>
            <li>½ tsp Salt</li>
            <li>½ cup Water (or as needed)</li>
            <li>1 tbsp Oil</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>For Stuffing:</h2>
        <ul class="ingredients-list">
            <li>1 cup Boiled & Mashed Potatoes</li>
            <li>½ cup Grated Paneer</li>
            <li>½ tsp Red Chili Powder</li>
            <li>½ tsp Garam Masala</li>
            <li>½ tsp Cumin Powder</li>
            <li>Salt to taste</li>
            <li>2 tbsp Coriander Leaves (chopped)</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Instructions:</h2>
        <ol class="instructions-list">
            <li>Mix wheat flour, salt, and water to knead a soft dough. Cover and let it rest for 15 minutes.</li>
            <li>In a bowl, mix mashed potatoes, paneer, spices, and coriander leaves for the stuffing.</li>
            <li>Divide the dough into equal portions and roll each into a small circle.</li>
            <li>Place a spoonful of stuffing in the center and seal the edges.</li>
            <li>Roll it out gently into a flat paratha.</li>
            <li>Heat a tawa and cook the paratha on both sides with ghee or butter.</li>
            <li>Serve hot with curd and pickle.</li>
        </ol>
    </div>

</body>
